               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17630706-2-off7-c38" targOrder="Y" targets="t17630706-2-defend40 t17630706-2-off7 t17630706-2-verdict10"></join>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17630706-2-off11-c38" targOrder="Y" targets="t17630706-2-defend40 t17630706-2-off11 t17630706-2-verdict10"></join>
         
               <p>259. (L.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17630706-2-defend40" type="defendantName">
                     Thomas 
                     Pearson 
                  <interp inst="t17630706-2-defend40" type="surname" value="Pearson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17630706-2-defend40" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17630706-2-defend40" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t17630706-2-off7" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17630706-2-off7" type="offenceCategory" value="damage"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17630706-2-off7" type="offenceSubcategory" value="arson"></interp>
               wilfully and unlawfully setting fire to the dwelling-house of his master
            </rs>, 
               
                  <persName id="t17630706-2-victim42" type="victimName">
                     John 
                     Ortell 
                  <interp inst="t17630706-2-victim42" type="surname" value="Ortell"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17630706-2-victim42" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17630706-2-victim42" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17630706-2-off7 t17630706-2-victim42"></join>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17630706-2-off11 t17630706-2-victim42"></join>
                  </persName>
                
            , in <placeName id="t17630706-2-crimeloc8">Prince's-street, Lothbury</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17630706-2-crimeloc8" type="placeName" value="Prince's-street, Lothbury"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17630706-2-crimeloc8" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17630706-2-off7 t17630706-2-crimeloc8"></join>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17630706-2-off11 t17630706-2-crimeloc8"></join>, <rs id="t17630706-2-cd9" type="crimeDate">May 23</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17630706-2-off7 t17630706-2-cd9"></join>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17630706-2-off11 t17630706-2-cd9"></join>. ||</p>
               <p>It appeared, the prisoner had set fire to the bed-curtains in a two pair of stairs room, and put it out himself, and about a quarter of an hour after he set<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="176307060003"></xptr> fire to a window-curtain in the dining-room; he confessed he did it with a poker from the kitchen-fire on the same floor, it was extinguished by timely assistance before it had done any farther damage than burning the curtain and some part of the wainscot. <rs id="t17630706-2-verdict10" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17630706-2-verdict10" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17630706-2-verdict10" type="verdictSubcategory" value="nonComposMentis"></interp>
               Diverse persons gave evidence of the insanity of his mind; on which account he was Acquitted
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>He was a second time indicted for <rs id="t17630706-2-off11" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17630706-2-off11" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17630706-2-off11" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing four linnen shirts, val. 14 s. and one neckcloth, val. 6 d.
            </rs> the property of 
               <persName id="t17630706-2-person43">
                  John 
                  Ortell 
               <interp inst="t17630706-2-person43" type="surname" value="Ortell"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17630706-2-person43" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17630706-2-person43" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>Without examining the evidences, he was <rs id="t17630706-2-verdict12" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17630706-2-verdict12" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               Acq.
            </rs>
               </p>
            </div1>
